      • addResidueAdjustment

        public void addResidueAdjustment(SequenceAnnotationGenerator.AnnotationGeneratorResult.ResidueAdjustment adjustment)
        Adds a residue insertion, deletion or adjustment to be applied to the sequence. Adjustments are applied in the order they are supplied after any annotations have been removed, and before any annotations are added. The residue positions specified by any later adjustments, must compensate for any earlier adjustments applied by this AnnotationGeneratorResult. For example, if you wish to delete the first 2 and the last 2 residues of the sequence GATTACA, then the following pairs of adjustments will produce equivalent results:
        new ResidueAdjustment(0,2,""), new ResidueAdjustment(3,5,"")
        new ResidueAdjustment(5,7,""), new ResidueAdjustment(0,2,"")
        Parameters:
        adjustment - the adjustment to apply to the sequence.
